The paper deals with multiuser scheduling in a cellular system, which involves information theory (IT) and networking (NI). The use of a Partially Observable Markov Decision Process (POMDP) suggests a focus on systems (SY) and decision making. The study of the implementation structure of the greedy policy suggests a focus on game theory (GT) and algorithms (LG).
